        <tr>
          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              Hi all,<br /><br />I am pondering getting an espresso maker (to make machhiatos as thats what I like - that touch of frothed milk makes for a smoother shot).  You can drop anywhere from 300-2,000 bucks on one no problem.  It seems to me the biggest difference once you start going up the scale is that you pick up 'pid' in the maker once yot get to the 800 dollar range and up.  That step seems to be the biggest contributor to price differential and as such I am wondering how much it is really worth.<br /><br />Any thoughts here?  Is PID really 'the shit' or can I shave off cost and be 90% as happy with 40% of the cost?  The caveat here is I don't want to ever think 'oh, why didn't I drop that extra 200-500' to put me into PID land manufacturers.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
